channel.title: Useless?
channel.description: Useless? Well, my new house is almost finished being built and stuff. My parents stated to the builders/electrician that we wanted ethernet ports in each room for the computers, so that we could use the internet. They installed Cat 5E cables in the walls, but the socket is just a phone port. I am like "WTF! You fucking niggers. We wanted high speed lan, not low speed dial-up" So, are they useless or what?

en.wikipedia.org

Structured cabling

In telecommunications, structured cabling is building or campus cabling infrastructure that consists of a number of standardized smaller elements (hence structured) called subsystems. Structured cabling is the design and installation of a cabling system that will support multiple hardware uses and be suitable for today’s needs and those of the future. With a correctly installed system, current and future requirements can be met, and hardware that is added in the future will be supported Struct...

item.title: Useless?
item.dc:creator: @bloodrayne bloodrayne
item.description:
@bloodrayne wrote:

Are you sure they even installed the wall plates yet? :o

Idk, maybe they misunderstood you. You’re talking about the lan plugin things, like at schools and such?

And if they are just regular phone jacks, they are still useful. They carry a good 50 volts through them at all time, use them to run a light or something when the power goes out Just don’t do anything stupid, the resistance of phone wires is like .01. Which means your wires will burn, since they’re not connected to breakers.
